  { depth:'greater-depth', gen:function(){ return { q:"The water cycle, carbon cycle, and nitrogen cycle are all described as 'cycles'. What does this imply about the matter involved?", opts:["Matter is continuously recycled — atoms move between living organisms and the environment repeatedly","New matter is created in each cycle","Matter is destroyed when organisms die","Each cycle only operates in one ecosystem"], c:0, e:"In biogeochemical cycles, atoms (e.g. carbon, water molecules) are never created or destroyed — they continuously cycle between living organisms, the atmosphere, oceans, and rocks." }; }}
